  "doc_id": "8919",
  "text": "Let F n = (M, F ) be a Finsler space over a connected n-dimensional base manifold M with a regular, 1 + -homogeneous and strongly convex Finsler metric (fundamental function, Finsler function) F [CITATION_1] . F n or F is said to be locally projectively flat (locally projectively Euclidean or, by M. Matsumoto's terminology, a Finsler space with rectilinear extremals) if there exists an atlas (U α , ϕ α ) α∈A of M satisfying the following condition: for any geodesic γ : I → U α of F n there exists a strictly monotone smooth function f : I → R, and two vectors a, b ∈ R n , a = 0 such that (1a) ϕ α (γ(t)) = f (t)a + b, t ∈ I.",
